717594f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 60th Street
717594f-a.text:
Broadway, west side, from 60th to 61st Streets. The building in
the foreground was built two years before this as a three-story
building. Nine stories have just been added, to make it a twelve-
story building. Construction work, both exterior and interior, was
completed within three months.
December 26, 1924.
Crossman.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

717592f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 60th Street (West)
717592f-a.text:
,29-~ N-'
Broadway, north from but not including West 60th Street, showing
the construction of the Interboroug Rapid Transit Co. subway. In the
center background (building with dome) is seen the High School for
Commerce, on the north side of West 65th Street, between Ninth and Tenth
Aves.
March 19, 1901.
Board of Transportation photograph.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
William B. Parsons Collection.

717596f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 60th Street
717596f-a.text:
1849 Broadway, west side, between 60th and 61st Streets. This
building will still stand in 1934.
About 1914.
W. D. Hassler.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
